Cell.Text: [S] G|You... you found her? I can't believe it. Let the girl come with me and we can begin her preparation. | I will send word to her family that she is in good hands. | You've truly earned the Blessing of Dibella, child. Prostrate yourself before her altar, and she will bestow her gift.
You just can't leave well enough alone, can you?
And just what do you think you're doing?
Unfortunately for you, we don't allow men into the inner sanctum.
Unfortunately for you, we don't allow the uninitiated into the inner sanctum.

Node.Caption: T01HamalConfrontNiceOption: I was curious about the temple.

Cell.Text: I heard there was a valuable statue here.
There are many valuable artifacts all through the temple.

Node.Caption: T01HamalConfrontMeanOption: This statue looks valuable.

Cell.Text: You have committed a breach, and must pay the penalty.
Luckily for you, there are more pressing matters. We could make an example of you, but perhaps you could be put to better use.

The ceremony you so rudely interrupted was the Exalted Protocol of the Dibellan Sybil. | I don't expect you to know what that means. | Suffice to say that our Sybil was recently lost to us. | Through the Protocol, we have seen the home of the next Sybil, to the north, in a small village pressed against the stone. | If you can travel there, and retrieve our young Sybil, your transgression will be forgiven.
[S] G|So be it. We gave you a choice.
I'm not your errand girl. The chalice is mine!
[S] G|So be it. We gave you a choice.

Node.Caption: T01HamalScrewYou: I'm not your errand boy. The chalice is mine!

Cell.Text: [S] We believe the place in our vision to be Karthwasten. | Now move quickly. The girl must be brought to the temple as soon as possible.

Node.Caption: T01HamalIGuessIllHelp: I will undertake this penance. Where is the village?
